  "text": "The role of steroids in the treatment of PIGN/IRGN is controversial. There is anecdotal evidence supporting the use of steroids, but in some studies, no correlation was found between steroid use and outcome [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In this retrospective analysis, we studied nine cases of PIGN/IRGN with crescents in adults to see if there is a correlation between the severity of presentation, steroid treatment, histological severity and outcome.",
